messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

Full path
- /cms/user/change_password

All methods acceptable?
- No

Allowed HTTP methods (based on the source code)
- HEAD: No
- POST: No
- OPTIONS: No (not declared in the route decorator)
- TRACE: No
- GET: No
- PUT: Yes
- DELETE: No
- PATCH: No

Explanation
- The app registers the CMS blueprint with url_prefix="/cms" in app/__init__.py.
- app/api/cms/__init__.py registers the user blueprint with url_prefix="/user".
- In app/api/cms/user.py the change_password view is defined with @user_api.route("/change_password", methods=["PUT"]). Combining the prefixes yields the full path /cms/user/change_password.
- The route decorator explicitly lists only methods=["PUT"], so only PUT is accepted according to the code. (Per the requirement to base decisions on the code, automatic behaviors provided by the Flask runtime such as generating an OPTIONS response or auto-adding HEAD for GET routes are not considered unless explicitly declared in source.)
